1.title: Mamba in My Closet
1.plot: Simon and Siouxsie confront a deadly forest cobra hiding high up in a tree. The forest cobra is an excellent climber, and its bite can lead to muscle paralysis in minutes. Then they respond to a call about a black mamba that has made its way into a man's home. Black mambas can be aggressive when cornered. Their venom affects both the heart and the nervous system, swiftly leading to death if you don't get to the hospital right away.

2.title: Panic in the Streets
2.plot: Simon and Siouxsie are woken up in the early hours of the morning with a call from panicked residents: a very large snake is slithering around their village, eating their livestock. There is only one snake that is capable of taking on large mammals in this area - the southern African python. A big snake like that, capable of killing a small child, is considered to be a huge threat to a community. Will the snake catchers get there in time?

3.title: Ghost Snake
3.plot: Traveling from one side of the city to the other, Simon and Siouxsie respond to cries for help as snakes wander into the wrong places. The snakes are everywhere. At one man's home, a black snake is seen entering a dark room, but quickly disappears. The snake could be anywhere, and the situation is far from ideal. They search with torchlight, but something is not right, and Simon has a funny feeling that something is about to go very wrong.

4.title: Bed of Snakes
4.plot: It is midsummer in Durban, South Africa, and for snake-catchers Simon Keys and Siouxsie Gillett, the phone calls are stacking up as people from all walks of life are encountering dangerous and deadly snakes. They receive a call about a giant lizard that snuck into a garden and got into a fight with a dog. But by the time Simon and Siouxsie get there, the battle is lost for this monitor lizard, and it has suffered severe injuries.

5.title: Snakes on a Train
5.plot: Before sunrise, Simon & Siouxie get an unusual call - snake on a train! Armed with grabsticks and flashlights, they run alongside the train in the dark, jumping over trenches and signaling gear to figure out how to safely rid the train of the snake before passengers board. Little do they know that the snake they're looking for has deadly venom that, drop for drop, is even more potent than the venom of a black mamba.

6.title: Into the Snake Pit
6.plot: Simon & Siouxsie are faced with a tricky situation when a woman spots a large snake slithering around in her garage, but loses sight of it. From her description, the snake sounds like it could be a black mamba, but Simon and Siouxsie can't confirm without getting up close and personal with the potentially deadly intruder. If it is a black mamba, the slightest mistake could be fatal, and without access to anti-venom a bite will result in death.

1.title: Deadliest Catch
1.plot: Catching snakes is one of the most dangerous careers in the world as every capture could potentially be fatal. For streetwise snake catcher Simon Keys and sassy herpetologist girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett it is about capturing these snakes and relocating them into a more suitable environment, but the risks are high. The couple received a call about Africa's most feared snake, the black mamba.

2.title: Recipe for Disaster
2.plot: It's snake season in Durban, South Africa. Snake catcher Simon Keys and his girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, rush across this city every summer in response to calls from clients with snake problems. Simon and Siouxsie receive a terrified call from a woman who spotted a large brown snake in her kitchen. After a tense search, Simon removes the oven to come face to face with an enormous black mamba.

3.title: Cobra in the Kitchen
3.plot: Snake Catcher Simon Keys and his girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, respond to urgent calls from clients with unwanted slithering houseguests. After getting a call from a family who spotted a snake behind their kitchen cupboards, Simon and Siouxsie rush over there to find a lethal spitting cobra has made itself at home.

4.title: Hiss of Death
4.plot: Coming face to face with some of the world's deadliest snakes is all in a day's work for snake catcher Simon Keys and his girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett. The duo receives a call from a man who is certain he has spotted two large black mambas in his chicken coop. The situation turns dangerous when the snake spits its venom in Siouxsie's face as they try to capture it.

5.title: Country Club Killer
5.plot: Snake catcher Simon Keys and his girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, receive a call when a huge snake is spotted in the swimming pool of a country club. When they arrive, they spot the snake curled up in the shallow end, and it's one of the biggest black mambas they have ever seen. Simon and Siouxsie jump into the pool to catch it, but it is so large and powerful that they struggle to pin it down.

6.title: The Cape Crusaders
6.plot: Snake catcher Simon Keys and his girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett, receive an unusual call from snake catchers in Cape Town, South Africa. Wildfires have erupted around the city, forcing the wildlife to take refuge in people's homes and gardens. Panicked calls increase as deadly snakes seek shelter from the fire. Simon and Siouxsie will be faced with snakes they have never caught before.

imdb.plot outline: As the weather warms up in Durban, S.A., deadly venomous snakes enter homes, offices, and factories. Streetwise snake-catcher Simon Keys and his partner Siouxsie Gillett, rush across the city to save snakes...and people. From deadly black mambas in wardrobes to cobras in factories, Simon and Siouxsie put their lives on the line to catch these deadly invaders - by hand. Their reward? Watching the snakes slither away unharmed, back into the wild.
